MAR 1578":"20 March 1578","Hennock, Devon, England, United Kingdom":"Hennock, Devon, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Radford","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Scottish: habitational name from any of several places called Radford (Devon, Nottinghamshire, Oxfordshire, Somerset, Warwickshire, Worcestershire), Raddiford (Devon), Ratford (Sussex, Wiltshire), Redford (Angus, Fife, Midlothian, Dorset, Sussex), Retford (Nottinghamshire), Rodford (Gloucestershire), or Rudford (Gloucestershire). Most of these placenames appear to derive from Old English <i>rēad</i> ‘red’ + <i>ford</i> ‘ford’, though some are likely to derive from Old English <i>hrēod</i> ‘reed’ + <i>ford</i> (e.g. Rodford and Rudford (Gloucestershire)), and the Oxfordshire placename may derive from Old English <i>rād</i> ‘riding’ + <i>ford</i>, probably meaning ‘ford which can be crossed on horseback’. This English name has been established in Ireland (Wexford) since the 16th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Redifer","meanings":["Possibly English: variant of <b>Reddiford</b>, itself a variant of   Radford  ."]},{"name":"Redford","meanings":["English: variant of   Radford  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Radford was born in 1495, in Hennock, Devon, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert Radford, was 33 and his mother, Elizabeth Mores, was 23. He had at least 1 son. He died on 20 March 1578, in his hometown, at the age of 83."},"et":{"1495–20 MAR 1578":"1495–20. märts 1578","1495–1578":"1495–1578","1510–1575":"1510–1575","1462–Male":"1462–Surnud","1472–Female":"1472–Surnud","1578":"1578","1510":"1510","1575":"157